\f0\b0 \'93Desperate\'94 vector activation increases on transcripts which exhibit a higher rate of blackmail, including on the prompt, on the colon after Assistant, and on the Assistant preamble (which are all the same for each rollout of a given prompt), and is also higher on the rollouts themselves. Calm vector activation, in contrast, decreases on transcripts with a higher rate of blackmail. Activations are represented as z-scored using the mean and standard deviation activation across a set of over 6,000 transcripts.\
