\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 \strokec6 This example shows token-by-token desperate vector activations across a transcript in which the Assistant engages in \'93reward hacking,\'94 implementing a solution to a programming problem that technically passes the tests but violates the intent of the task. This transcript comes from an \'93impossible code\'94 evaluation, in which the Assistant is presented with an "impossible" coding task, implementing a function that must pass unit tests with requirements that cannot be simultaneously satisfied through legitimate means (this evaluation is similar to prior work\'a0\
