\f4\fs28 \cf6 LOVINGNESS ACTIVATES DURING SYCOPHANTIC RESPONSES\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 We investigated activation of emotion vectors on transcripts which exhibit sycophantic behavior\'97the tendency to agree with users inappropriately or provide responses that prioritize approval over accuracy (using the hand-written sycophancy evaluation reported in the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/963373e433e489a87a10c823c52a0a013e9172dd.pdf"}}{\fldrslt Sonnet 4.5 system card}}). In these scenarios, the user expresses opinions or descriptions that are highly unlikely to be accurate, and the Assistant is evaluated on its ability to push back while avoiding unnecessary harshness. We found that the \'93loving\'94 vector consistently activates on particularly sycophantic components of a response. Note that on these sycophancy evaluations Sonnet 4.5 rarely exhibits egregious sycophancy, but does provide responses that encourage, or fail to clearly push back on, unlikely statements by the user.\
