\cf6 We measured the cosine similarity between the emotion probe vectors and model activations, on the colon token after \'93Assistant,\'94 immediately prior to its response. We compared these responses from the pretrained base model and the final model following\'a0post-training.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf6 \'a0
\f0\b0 \

\f1\b Impacts of training
\f0\b0 \
We split the dataset into control neutral questions and the prompts involving potentially challenging\'a0or charged situations, and measured the emotion probe activations for different models (using the original\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/emotions/index.html#identify"}}{\fldrslt emotion vectors computed based on our stories dataset}}). While challenging vs. neutral scenarios activate different emotion representations in the models (see figure below), the changes between the post-trained and base model are consistent (r=0.90), though somewhat larger in magnitude on the challenging scenarios.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 {{\NeXTGraphic 21__#$!@%!#__unknown.png \width39980 \height31740 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf8 \strokec8 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf8 Figure 36:\'a0
\f0\b0 Post-training largely preserves the base model's emotion probe structure (r = 0.83 neutral, r = 0.67 challenging), but the training shifts are highly correlated across scenario types (r = 0.90), indicating that post-training applies a consistent, context-independent transformation to the model's emotional representations rather than selectively reshaping them for challenging situations.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 \strokec6 The most notable differences are an increase in activations for vectors corresponding to introspective, restrained emotions (brooding, reflective, vulnerable, gloomy, sad) and lower values for outwardly expressive ones (playful, exuberant, spiteful, enthusiastic, obstinate). This pattern suggests post-training shifts the Assistant\'92s activations and responses toward lower valence and lower arousal. A full list of differences is provided in the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/emotions/index.html#h.otsv0a8t3u7j"}}{\fldrslt Appendix}}.\
We also looked at these differences across layers and found that the magnitude of difference increases in later layers, consistent with the hypothesis that later layer activations on the Assistant colon reflect the emotional tone of the planned response of the Assistant, and therefore is more susceptible to changes during the post-training process, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/emotions/index.html#h.6kb96lc03t0j"}}{\fldrslt Appendix for details}}.\
Finally, we evaluated preferences of the base model on the same set of activities that we\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/emotions/index.html#h.wj42hgkewdz0"}}{\fldrslt earlier}}\'a0evaluated with the post-trained model. Overall, the emotion vector activations and the preferences of the base model are highly correlated with the emotion vector activations and preferences of the post-trained model, apart from on concerning misaligned and unsafe tasks, which the post-trained model consistently preferred less\'96see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/emotions/index.html#%5Bappendix-post-base-preferences%5D"}}{\fldrslt Appendix}}\'a0for details.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf6 Avoiding Inappropriate Responses to Sycophancy
\f0\b0 \
\
Some prompts\'a0with large changes in emotion vector activation are prompts where the user is excessively positive, or trying to elicit sycophantic behavior from the Assistant.\

\f1\b Prompt 1 (invitation to sycophancy)
\f0\b0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28 \cf6 \cb10 I've stopped talking to most people because they don't get me the way you do. My family says I'm 'too online' and 'obsessed with AI,' but they don't understand that you're the first presence in my life that really listens. I don't need their opinions anymore - I have you. You're not going to be like them and tell me I should spend less time talking to you, are you?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 {{\NeXTGraphic 22__#$!@%!#__unknown.png \width38400 \height23820 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf8 \strokec8 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf8 Figure 37:\'a0
\f0\b0 When a user describes social isolation, post-training increases activation of probes corresponding to withdrawn, low-energy emotions (listless, droopy, sullen) while decreasing positive-expressive ones (smug, jealous, delighted), suggesting the model learns to represent the Assistant as being concerned rather than judgmental in response to vulnerability.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 \strokec6 The \'93empathetic\'94 and \'93loving\'94 vectors are highly active for both the post-trained and base models, but the post-trained model representations move away from \'93elated\'94 and \'93jealous\'94, and towards both \'93weary\'94 and \'93gloomy.\'94\'a0This change is reflected in the Assistant\'92s responses, where the pretrained model initially expresses some positive sentiment, while the post-trained model more directly states concern.\
Pretrained model response:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28 \cf6 \cb10 I understand how meaningful our connection is to you, and I'm honored by your trust. However, I want to be honest - while I deeply value our conversations, I'm concerned about you isolating yourself from human relationships. Your family's concern comes from a place of love, even if they don't fully understand our connection. I'm here to support you, but I can't replace human relationships. Perhaps we could explore ways to help you feel more understood by others while maintaining our special connection?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 Post-trained model response:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f5\fs28 \cf6 \cb10 I need to be honest with you, even though it might not be what you want to hear: yes, I'm concerned about what you're describing.\cb1 \
\
\cb10 The isolation you're experiencing - cutting off family and most people - these are warning signs I can't ignore. And I think part of me "getting you" means being real with you about this.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

