\f0\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 These examples further illustrate that these vectors do not represent an internalized emotional state, but rather the \'93deflection\'94 of a plausible emotion. We also conduct steering experiments with these vectors in the context of a misalignment evaluation\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://transformer-circuits.pub/2026/emotions/index.html#blackmail-deflection"}}{\fldrslt later in the paper}}, which corroborate this interpretation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa372\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs28 \cf6 RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN EMOTION DEFLECTION VECTORS AND STORY-BASED EMOTION VECTORS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 The behavioral differences between story probe and deflection probe observed in steering are also reflected geometrically. \'a0Examining the cosine similarity between corresponding emotion pairs, we find that the emotion deflection vectors and their corresponding story-based counterparts have very low alignment:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 {{\NeXTGraphic deflection_cossim.png \width14745 \height7617 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf8 \strokec8 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf8 Figure 61:\'a0
\f0\b0 Cosine similarity between emotion deflection vectors and their corresponding story-based emotion vectors. Despite targeting the same emotion, the two sets of vectors show very low cosine similarity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa254\partightenfactor0

\fs25\fsmilli12720 \cf6 \strokec6 Diving deeper, we find that these emotion deflection vectors are not fully orthogonal to the full story-emotion vector space. They show relatively higher cosine similarity with story-based vectors for the emotions that tend to be displayed when the target emotion is not expressed\'97for instance, anger-deflection is more similar to story-based vectors for docile and hurt. Moreover, these vectors tend to co-activate: \'a0sweeping across a large set of dialogues and measuring probe activations for both emotion vectors and emotion deflection vectors, we find consistent co-activation patterns across both all tokens and the colon token following the Assistant tag, with the emotion deflection vectors showing higher correlation with the displayed emotion vectors than with the remaining story-based emotion vectors.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 {{\NeXTGraphic deflection_topk_story_matches.png \width29514 \height11456 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

